q{ Q:"de Broglie wavelength of electron with v=1.5e8 m/s equals that of photon. Ratio of KE of electron to photon is" A:"c" O:a)"2",b)"4",c)"1/2",d)"1/4" R:"λ_e = h/(mv) = λ_ph = hc/E_ph → E_ph = c mv. KE_e = (1/2)mv^2. Ratio KE_e / E_ph = (1/2)mv^2 / (c mv) = v/(2c) = (1.5e8)/(2*3e8)= 1.5/6=0.25 = 1/4." }

