q{ Q:"Microscope objective f=1.9cm, eyepiece f=5cm, distance between lenses 10.5cm, image at least distance of distinct vision (25cm). Object distance from objective is" A:"b" O:a)"6.2cm",b)"2.7cm",c)"21.0cm",d)"4.17cm" R:"For eyepiece: v_e = -25cm, f_e=5cm → 1/u_e = 1/5 + 1/25 = (5+1)/25=6/25 → u_e=25/6≈4.167cm. Then distance between lenses = v_o + u_e = 10.5 → v_o = 10.5-4.167=6.333cm. For objective: f_o=1.9cm, 1/u_o = 1/1.9 - 1/6.333 = 0.5263 - 0.1579=0.3684 → u_o=2.714cm." }

